pull_request.title: Add nix instructions for developers
pull_request.body:
The instructions for setting up using `nix` were not copied over when the nix setup was taken from https://github.com/pq-code-package/mlkem-c-embedded. I added them now. 

@hanno-becker does this contain all the information you were missing?

pull_request.title: Contract-based proofs of poly.c scalar_[de]compress_q*
pull_request.body:
This PR adds contract based CBMC proofs of four functions in mlkem/poly.c
 scalar_compress_q_16
 scalar_compress_q_32
 scalar_decompress_q_16
 scalar_decompress_q_32

No functional change.

review.body: As mentioned, I prefer to avoid cluttering the code with `#pragma`s and disable the overflow check at the function-level. But this can be changed in a separate PR. Thanks @rod-chapman !
